PMID== 8848425
TI  == [cytolysins and homologous proteins produced by gram-negative bacteria. i. hemolysis and leukotoxins of escherichia coli, bordetella pertussis, pasteurella  haemolytica and actinobacillus sp].
AB  == cytolysins produced by gram-negative bacteria belong to the pore forming bacterial proteins. a branch of these toxins represents rtx family of proteins. the rtx (repeats in toxin) family name has been proposed based on the common presence of tandem copies of a nine-amino acid repeat (l-x-g-g-x-g-(n/d)-d-x). the paper presents the genetics, synthesis, secretion and cytolytic activity of these toxins.
TIHT== 
